338	\section{Cohomology of an open in \texorpdfstring{$\ModuleCat\,k$}{ModuleCat k} flavor (iter-013)}
339	\label{sec:hmodule_prime}
340	
341	The iter-013 work scaffolds a new declaration $\HModulePrime$ in \texttt{Cohomology/StructureSheafModuleK.lean}, parallel to Mathlib's \lstinline{Sheaf.H' F n X} (file \texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/Basic.lean}, L105) for $\AddCommGrpCat$-valued sheaves. The new declaration is the \emph{cohomology of an open} in $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavor, the API entry point that downstream Mayer-Vietoris LES (queued iter-014+) and Čech-vs-derived-functor comparison theorems (queued iter-015+) both consume.
