352	  where $\mathtt{free}_k := \ModuleCat.\mathtt{free}\,k : \mathrm{Type}\,u \to \ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k$ is Mathlib's free $k$-module functor (\texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Category/ModuleCat/Adjunctions.lean}). Carries a $\Module\,k$ instance through the same $\HasExt$ + $\Linear\,k$ chain that powers $\HModule$, accessible via the \lstinline{noncomputable abbrev} reducibility — under \lstinline{def}, instance synthesis would fail (cf. iter-009 design rationale).
