365	\begin{remark}[Why this is the iter-013 target, not the iso \texorpdfstring{$\HModulePrime\,F\,n\,\top \cong \HModule\,F\,n$}{H'(F)(top) ≅ H(F)}]
366	  Mathlib's \texttt{Basic.lean} (lines 30–35) explicitly leaves the iso $\HModule\,F\,n \cong (\mathtt{cohomologyPresheaf}\,F\,n).\mathrm{obj}\,(\mathrm{op}\,U)$ for $U$ terminal as a \texttt{TODO}: it is not currently proved in Mathlib for $\AddCommGrpCat$-valued sheaves. We do not attempt it here either — iter-013 only adds the API; Mathlib will catch up to the iso. Iter-014+ will define the $\cohomologyPresheaf$ functor, after which the iso (when Mathlib provides it) propagates to $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavor for free.
